# Credit Risk Scorecard (Baseline Model)

This script builds a basic credit risk scorecard using the German Credit dataset. The goal is to estimate default risk and convert it into a simple, interpretable credit score.

## Approach

* Convert target variable to default (1 = bad, 0 = good)
* Split data into training and testing sets
* Apply WOE (Weight of Evidence) transformation
* Fit a logistic regression model using all variables
* Evaluate performance using ROC, AUC, and KS
* Build a scorecard and generate borrower scores

## Output

* ROC curve and AUC
* KS statistic
* Credit score distribution
* Decision rule: approve if score > 600

## Notes

This version uses all variables after WOE transformation and serves as a baseline model to understand the full scorecard pipeline.
